{"comments":"CubicBezierEasing — Molecule composing bezier control points for easing curves.\n\n## CSS cubic-bezier()\n\nThe standard timing function for CSS animations:\n  cubic-bezier(x1, y1, x2, y2)\n\nThe curve goes from (0,0) to (1,1), with control points P1 and P2.\n\n## Standard CSS Keywords\n\n- **ease**: (0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1.0)\n- **ease-in**: (0.42, 0, 1, 1)\n- **ease-out**: (0, 0, 0.58, 1)\n- **ease-in-out**: (0.42, 0, 0.58, 1)\n- **linear**: (0, 0, 1, 1)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["x1",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","BezierParam"],"CubicX1"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["y1",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","BezierParam"],"CubicY1"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["x2",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","BezierParam"],"CubicX2"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["y2",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","BezierParam"],"CubicY2"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[116,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/CubicBezierEasing.purs","start":[111,27]},"title":"CubicBezierEasing"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","CubicBezierEasing"],"CubicBezierEasing"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[118,60],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/CubicBezierEasing.purs","start":[118,1]},"title":"eqCubicBezierEasing"},{"